CHANGES0014: NormalForms.agda — DNF support added (425 lines, was 314)

Added DNF syntactic operations:
- andClauseDNF: distribute single conjunctive clause over DNF
- andDNF: AND of two DNFs (distribute ∧ over ∨)
- negConjToDNF: negate a conjunctive clause to DNF
- negDNF: negate a DNF
- xorDNF: XOR of two DNFs via (d₁∨d₂) ∧ ((1+d₁)∨(1+d₂))
- termToDNF: convert freeBA term to DNF

Added DNF correctness proofs (all compiling, no holes):
- evalDNF-++: evalDNF distributes over list concatenation
- evalConjLits-++: evalConjLits distributes over list concatenation
- andClauseDNF-correct: uses evalConjLits-++ and ∧DistR∨
- andDNF-correct: uses evalDNF-++, andClauseDNF-correct, ∧DistL∨
- negConj-correct: uses evalLit-neg and compl-or-is-compl-and
- negDNF-correct: uses andDNF-correct, negConj-correct, compl-and-is-compl-or
- xorDNF-correct: uses andDNF-correct, evalDNF-++, negDNF-correct, xor-via-cnf

Added DNF surjectivity:
- termToDNF-correct: proved by structural induction on terms
- dnfSurj: (x : ⟨ freeBA A ⟩) → ∥ hasDNF x ∥₁

The DNF proofs are exactly dual to the CNF proofs, reusing the same
Boolean algebra identities (compl-or-is-compl-and, compl-and-is-compl-or,
xor-via-cnf, etc.).

Remaining postulates: NONE
File compiles successfully.
